==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[habilement]]'', from Old French ''[[habillement]]'' "to clothe".

===Pronunciation===
(US) IPA: /həˈbɪlɪmənt/

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# [[clothes|Clothes]], especially clothing [[appropriate]] for someone's job, status, or to an occasion.
